text: Acleris leechi is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae. It is found in Korea, China, Japan (Hokkaido, Honshu, Yokohama, Shikoku) and Russia (Ussuri, Vladivostok, eastern Siberia). The wingspan is 13–17 mm.Check List of the Tribe Tortricini (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae) in Northeast china, with Two Newly Recorded Species from China The larvae feed on Quercus species.Croesia at funet ==References== Category:Moths described in 1900 leechi Category:Moths of Asia
